{"questionId": "f5cee4a9-66e4-4bd3-a039-2e4ea1aa7776_18", "correctAnswer": "D", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Solve the system by elimination", "content": "Subtract: $(\\tfrac{5}{4}x+2y)-(\\tfrac{3}{4}x+2y)=17-15$, so $\\tfrac{1}{2}x=2\\Rightarrow x=4$. Then $\\tfrac{3}{4}(4)+2y=15$ gives $y=6$."}, {"title": "Find $\\tfrac{11}{4}x + 6y$", "content": "Compute: $\\tfrac{11}{4}(4)+6(6)=11+36=47$. That matches choice <strong>D</strong> — <strong>D</strong> is correct."}]}